        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "Shabbat Candle Blessing - The mitzvah of kindling Shabbat lights in the home is an early rabbinic\npractice (M. Shabbat 2:1ff.) The Shabbat candle blessing is first recorded in the ninth-century\nprayerbook, Seder Rav Amram. Lighting Shabbat candles as part of the synagogue service is an\ninnovation of Reform Judaism.",
